OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1783779570
OL,3,CMan fined #40,000 for unlicensed tree
OL,4,Cfelling and habitat damage
OL,6,FA 40-year-old man has been fined for
OL,7,Funlicensed tree felling and habitat
OL,8,Fdamage in Horsham.
OL,10,FThe destruction took place in March
OL,11,F2022 across an 11 acre site in Horsham.
OL,13,FEcological reports by Forestry England
OL,14,Fhighlighted that the area that was
OL,15,Fhome to a protected wildlife species,
OL,16,Fthe Great Crested Newt. But Rural
OL,17,FCrime Team officers attended the site
OL,18,Fon 23 March 2022 to find a vast area
OL,19,Fof trees had been felled.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1783779570
OL,3,CMan fined #40,000 for unlicensed tree
OL,4,Cfelling and habitat damage
OL,6,FOfficers were told by the contractors
OL,7,Fthat they had been deceived by Paul
OL,8,FWelch, owner of Oakmount Parks ltd the
OL,9,Fcompany they were contracted to, that
OL,10,Fecology reports showed that no Great
OL,11,FCrested Newts were at the site.
OL,13,FSpeaking to officers, Welch claimed
OL,14,Fhe'd only ordered for trees damaged by
OL,15,FStorm Eunice, as well as those that
OL,16,Fwere already dying to be felled,
OL,17,Fstating it would have been a risk for
OL,18,Fthe trees to stay up. He also claimed
OL,19,Fthat he'd never had a visit from the
OL,20,FForest Commission ordering him to stop
OL,21,Fcutting town the trees.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1783779570
OL,3,CMan fined #40,000 for unlicensed tree
OL,4,Cfelling and habitat damage
OL,6,FHowever, there had been a site visit
OL,7,Fby Horsham District Council
OL,8,FArboriculture officers who noted that
OL,9,Fmany of the trees being felled weren't
OL,10,Fstorm damaged and dying, but fresh and
OL,11,Fgreen, and told workers at the site to
OL,12,Fstop. However, Welch ignored this and
OL,13,Fthe site was cleared.
OL,15,FWelch admitted at interview that he
OL,16,Fdidn't read the ecological reports
OL,17,Fthat he had commissioned to gain
OL,18,Fplanning permission in full.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1783779570
OL,3,CMan fined #40,000 for unlicensed tree
OL,4,Cfelling and habitat damage
OL,6,FThese reports stated that Great
OL,7,FCrested Newts were living in or near
OL,8,Ftwo of the 11 ponds within the land.
OL,9,FThis section of the report Welch said
OL,10,Fhe had read and he knew the animals
OL,11,Fwere present on the plot of land he
OL,12,Fwanted to clear to build a number of
OL,13,Fwood cabins.
OL,15,FWelch then went on to confirm that he
OL,16,Fwas aware that it is illegal to carry
OL,17,Fout work without a European Protected
OL,18,FSpecies (EPS) licence from Natural
OL,19,FEngland as well as having planning
OL,20,Fpermission.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1783779570
OL,3,CMan fined #40,000 for unlicensed tree
OL,4,Cfelling and habitat damage
OL,6,FHe confirmed that he knew Great
OL,7,FCrested Newts were a species protected
OL,8,Fby law. He also confirmed that he knew
OL,9,Ffelling the trees would disturb the
OL,10,Fnewts and could destroy their habitat.
OL,11,FBut he claimed that he only ordered
OL,12,Fthe trees to be felled for health and
OL,13,Fsafety reasons.
OL,15,FAn ecologist who visited the site
OL,16,Fconcluded that it was highly likely
OL,17,Fthat Great Crested Newts and any other
OL,18,Fanimal at the site would have been
OL,19,Fkilled, and their habitats and nests
OL,20,Falmost completely destroyed and
OL,21,Funlikely to recover.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1783779570
OL,3,CMan fined #40,000 for unlicensed tree
OL,4,Cfelling and habitat damage
OL,6,FThe ecologist also explained that not
OL,7,Fonly did Welch's claims of felling
OL,8,Ftrees for health and safety reasons
OL,9,Fnot add up, due to how the trees had
OL,10,Fbeen felled and how many had been cut
OL,11,Fdown, the site was now actually more
OL,12,Fdangerous with trees that would
OL,13,Fotherwise have been protected left
OL,14,Fexposed.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1783779570
OL,3,CMan fined #40,000 for unlicensed tree
OL,4,Cfelling and habitat damage
OL,6,FFollowing an extensive and complex
OL,7,Finvestigation, Welch was charged by
OL,8,Fpostal requisition with damaging or
OL,9,Fdestroying a breeding site or resting
OL,10,Fplace of a wild animal of a European
OL,11,Fprotected species, and felling a
OL,12,Fgrowing tree without a felling licence.
OL,14,FWelch pleaded guilty to both offences
OL,15,Fat Worthing Magistrates' Court and was
OL,16,Ffined #40,000 and ordered to pay a
OL,17,Fsurcharged and court costs totalling
OL,18,F#3,000.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
